# TypeScript (.ts) — condensed

Aligned with `.claude/rules/typescript-conventions.md` and coding-standards.

- Keep **cyclomatic complexity ≤ 6** for all non-TSX TypeScript; fail fast at module boundaries where appropriate.
- **Service layer:** browser data through Supabase service patterns; cohesive mapping; no service role client in the browser.
- **API routes:** admin client server-only; validate inputs; clear HTTP semantics; typed payloads shared via project types modules.
- **lib / scripts:** narrow utilities; explicit errors for programmer mistakes; scripts assume secrets stay off the client bundle.

Product-specific constraints stay in CLAUDE.md / agents.md.
